[TODO] BUG: (do (id-fn arg) other) returns nil when id-fn is the literal
       identity (def f (x) x). Reproduces under bytecode-only build (no
       JIT involvement). Repro: (def f (x) x); (prn (do (f 1) 42))
       prints blank instead of 42. Workaround in test.alc uses (+ x 1)
       in the JIT loop+call test. Suspect interaction between identity
       lambda's bytecode (LOAD_SLOT 0; RET) and the OP_POP that compile_do
       inserts after the call. Discovered while wiring (do ...) into the
       compiler — pre-existing issue surfaced once that path went live.

